Taiwan Stocks: Epistar, Highwealth Construction, Hung Poo

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-03-07T05:59:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/taiwan-stocks-epistar-highwealth-construction-hung-poo.html
Stocks of the following companies
had unusual price changes in Taipei trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and shares are as 1:30 p.m. close.  Taiwan’s Taiex Index fell 70.61, or 0.8 percent, to
8,713.79.  Construction stocks:  Hung Poo Real Estate Development Corp. (2536) 
(2536 TT) slumped 6.6 percent to NT$36.90, the lowest since July
20.  Highwealth Construction Corp. (2542)  (2542 TT) dropped 5.8 percent
to NT$57.40, the most since July 26. The  finance ministry  has
submitted to the Cabinet a proposal for a new  sales tax  on
second homes sold within two years, Wu Lien-ying, director of
the ministry’s property tax division, said in a phone interview
today. The planned tax was reported earlier by the Commercial
Times.  Light-emitting diode companies:  Epistar Corp. (2448)  (2448 TT)
surged 6.8 percent to NT$109.50, the highest since April 9, and
Everlight Electronics Co. (2393 TT) gained 4.3 percent to
NT$88.20, the most since Sept. 10. Investors speculate China’s
focus on energy conservation to boost light-emitting diode
companies, said Cho Chih-Yun, an analyst at Mega Securities Co.  China  plans to implement preferential tax policies to encourage
job creation, energy conservation and a reduction in emissions,
the Ministry of Finance said in its 2011 budget report released
in Beijing March 5.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
